The paper deals with automated skin lesion analysis using deep learning models, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses biases in skin lesion datasets, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of models trained on small datasets, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
